        <updateDate>2022-08-02T16:53:29Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Relief for Families Act of 2022</strong></p> <p>This bill permits state and local coronavirus fiscal recovery funds to be used to address increased costs of essential items.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill authorizes a temporary suspension of sales taxes for essential items, including clothing that does not exceed $100 per item, food, diapers, feminine hygiene products, prescription and over-the-counter medicine, items to prepare for natural disasters or severe weather, school supplies, and energy efficient appliances.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
